<p>Laura McGrew Cambodia collection, #8895.  Rare and Manuscript Holdings of the Division of Asia Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_7269d7df53ff849e873c62c0e93431a8">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Laura McGrew is a consultant in the fields of human rights, reconciliation, and transitional justice in Cambodia (where she's worked since 1987) as well as Rwanda, Sri Lanka, Afghanistan, Nepal, and Bosnia. In addition to graduate degrees in medical science from Emory University and public policy from Johns Hopkins University's School of Advanced International Studies, McGrew received her PhD from Coventry University in 2011 upon the completion of her dissertation, "Reconciliation in Cambodia: victims and perpetrators living together, apart."</p>  </bioghist>
